TopicTitle: Kerbalism - Fuel cells dont work - Oxygen / Hydrogen tanks neither

Articles.Content:
Hello,

I have KSP 1.8, with kerbalism and CTT. 

Trying to get fuel cells to work, but they dont. The fuel cell says running, but there is no electricity generated. Also, the small pressurized containers seem to hold nothing. 

Any idea how  i can fix this? Solar panels are 90 science, I can't get that without working fuel cells.
Nevermind! |I did not have the resource pack installed. Working fine now!

On 11/7/2019 at 9:19 AM, PresFox said:

Nevermind! |I did not have the resource pack installed. Working fine now!

Which resource pack? Doesn't seem to be working here now either.

Fuel Cell is "running" but EC is not generated, and resources are not consumed.

UPDATE:
Nevermind. Doesn't work if containers are full and you forgot to set it to dump excess.
